{"word":"H7065 - קָנָא - qânâʼ - kaw-naw' - Envy","slug":"H7065","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">קָנָא</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>qânâʼ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kaw-naw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Envy"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E7;&#x05E0;&#x05D0; - qa&#x0302;na&#x0302;'</b> - <i>kaw-naw'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>be</i> (causatively <i>make</i>) <i>zealous</i>, that is, (in a bad sense) <i>jealous</i> or <i>envious: - </i> (be) envy (-ious), be (move to, provoke to) jealous (-y), X very, (be) zeal (-ous)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H7067\">H7067</a>, <a href=\"#/H7068\">H7068</a>, <a href=\"#/H7072\">H7072</a>"}]}